    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Nelson County was formed in 1807 from Amherst County.  The county was named for Thomas Nelson, Jr., governor of Virginia from June to November 1781.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Nelson County (Va.) Circuit Court Records, 1851-1922 are comprised of the following record types: Chancery Docket Books, Chancery Fee Books, Chancery Memorandum Books, a Chancery Minute Book, a Chancery Rule Docket Book, a Common Law Docket Book, a Clerk's Common Law Docket Book, Common Law Fee Books, Law Fee Books, Common Law Memorandum Books, a Common Law Minute Book, a Docket Book, Fee Books, an Issue Docket Book, a Jury List Book, a Minute Book, a Receipt Book for Chancery Causes, a Process Book and a Witness Attendance Book.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
